power-user-tool.POWER-USER-TOOL-TEXT: The Zebra Power User Tool is a windows based application. Here is how you can access it:
power-user-tool.FIRST-OPTION: Open a browser window on your windows based computer.
power-user-tool.SECOND-OPTION: Type in the following URL: zebra.com/123scan

check-power.IS-THE-GREEN-LED-ON-NOW: Is the green LED on now?
check-power.IS-THE-CABLE-INSERTED-TO-THE-SCANNER: Is the cable inserted to the scanner?
check-power.CONNECT-TO-SCANNER-ADDITIONAL-INFO:
Check the orientation; it only fits one way.
Push firmly until click.
check-power.MUST-BE-POWERED-USB-HUB: If using hub, it must be a “powered USB hub.”
check-power.RE-CHECK-CONNECTION-TO-SCANNER-DESCRIPTI:
1. Unplug cable.
2. Firmly reinsert, listen for click.
check-power.RE-CHECK-CONNECTION-TO-COMPUTER-DESCRIPT:
1. Ensure computer is on.
2. Try different computer USB port.
3. If using hub, it must be a “powered USB hub”
check-power.TRY-FIX-1-INFO: This barcode stops your scanner from "Pressing Enter" after each scan.
check-power.TRY-FIX-2-INFO: This barcode enables your scanner to "Press Tab" after each scan.
check-power.IS-BATTERY-INSERTED: Is the battery inserted into Scanner?
check-power.IS-CRADLE-GREEN-LED-ON: Is the cradle’s green LED on?
check-power.UNLOCK_BATTERY_DESCRIPTION:
1. Unlock battery latch with coin.
2. Insert battery and lock battery latch.
check-power.IS-CABLE-INSERTED-TO-CRADLE: Is cable inserted to the cradle?
check-power.IS-CRADLE-GREEN-LED-ON-NOW: Is the cradle’s green LED on now?
check-power.PLACE-SCANNER-ON-CRADLE-DESCRIPTION: Place scanner in cradle to pair with cradle.
check-power.PLACE-SCANNER-ON-CRADLE-ADDITIONAL-INFO: A beep on your scanner confirms successful pairing.
check-power.CONFIRM-SCANNER-IS-CHARGED-DESCRIPTION: If scanner does not produce a beam when triggered, seat scanner in cradle and allow time to achieve minimum charge to connect.
check-power.CONFIRM-SCANNER-IS-CHARGED-ADDITIONAL-IN: Red/amber/green lights indicate charge level. Wait for an amber charge level to pair scanner.
check-power.HAS-SCANNER-PAIRED-DESCRIPTION: If Scanner doesn’t pair, scan the pairing barcode on the cradle.

test-scan.DO-YOU-HEAR-A-BEEP-WHEN-SCANNING: Do you hear a beep when scanning?

success.SUCCESS-TEXT: Pick what you want to do next.

support.ZEBRA-WILL-HELP-YOU: Okay, Zebra support will help you resolve the issue.
support.CONTACT-ZEBRA-SUPPORT: Please contact Zebra support to receive further assistance.

buttons.CONFIGURE-ANOTHER-SCANNER-DESCRIPTION: Download configuration barcode to use for another scanner
